frameDefinitions: An Agent causes a Firearm to discharge which induces the rapid motion of the Projectile.
A Driver prepares a Vehicle for travel by placing it in the normal location for the operation of the vehicle or by detaching it from a place where it was held.
A Cause triggers a System to operate in accordance with its intended purpose.
An Agent acts to begin the life of a Process.
An Entity meets the pre-conditions for participating in an Event.
A Cook applies heat to Food, where the Temperature_setting of the heat and Duration of application may be specified.
frameExamples: The bank robber <t>shot</t> at the clerks with an AK-47.
Throughout Irish history, countless generations of exiles have <t>cast</t> <t>off</t> from the shores of Ireland.
Smoking a cigarette will normally not <t>set off</t> a smoke alarm.
After discovering her knack for organization, she decided to try to  <t>launch</t> a career in human resources.
Conductor software gives us the hands-on <t>capability</t> to provide updates immediately
listRoleDefinitions: The entity whose rapid, dangerous motion is caused by the Agent and/or Firearm.
The Agent is the person performing the intentional act causing the motion of the Projectile.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the shooting event takes place.
The location in which the shooting event takes place.
This is the being, typically human, that prepares the <fen>Vehicle</fen> for motion, and will control it once it is in motion.
The device--such as a car, boat, spaceship,. etc.--which is used for transport and is prepared for travel by the <fen>Driver</fen>.
Any expression which describes the location that the <fen>Vehicle</fen> has been stationed at.
The  <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Driver</fen> prepares the <fen>Vehicle</fen> for motion.
The <fen>Place</fen> describes the location where the <fen>Driver</fen> prepares the <fen>Vehicle</fen> for motion.
The <fen>Cause</fen> interacts with the <fen>System</fen> such that conditions are met for the <fen>System</fen> to operate.
The <fen>System</fen> interacts with or detects the <fen>Cause</fen> and activates.
An entity which participates in a <fen>Cause</fen>, perhaps volitionally and perhaps not.
The time when the triggering takes place.
Where the triggering takes place.
This Frame Element marks expressions that indicate the process that the <fen>Agent</fen> initiates.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is the actor responsible for starting the <fen>Process</fen>.
This role is for the <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Agent</fen> initiates the <fen>Process</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Process</fen> is initiated.
The <fen>Entity</fen> whose meeting or falling short of pre-conditions is assessed.
The time at which the <fen>Entity</fen> is capable of the <fen>Event</fen>.
The <fen>Cook</fen> applies heat to the <fen>Food</fen>.
This role identifes the entity that  directly supplies heat to the <fen>Food</fen>.
<fen>Food</fen> is the entity to which heat is applied by the <fen>Cook</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Temperature_setting</fen> of the <fen>Heating_instrument</fen> for the <fen>Food</fen>.
The <fen>Container</fen> holds the <fen>Food</fen> to which heat is applied.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> at which the heat application occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the heat application  occurs.
